The paper discusses the definition and development of ontologies, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) for knowledge representation and reasoning. It also touches on the role of annotations and collaborative development, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). Additionally, ontologies are often stored and queried in databases (cs.DB).
